# k6 / prod bring-up (split data + app plane) — **not** a replacement for **`infra/dev/.env.example`**.
# Copy the lines you need into a repo-root **`.env`** (gitignored) for **`docker compose --env-file`**, or use as a checklist while editing **`infra/prod/.env.app.example`**
# / **`infra/prod/.env.data.example`**. **Never** commit real secrets.
#
# Runbook: `docs/prod-runbook.md` · **Secrets:** `docs/prod-secrets.md`

# --- App host — messaging-service + RabbitMQ (placeholders) ---
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://mongo.biratbhattacharjee.com:27017/messaging
REDIS_URL=redis://<data-hostname-or-IP>:6379
S3_ENDPOINT=http://<data-hostname-or-IP>:9000
PUBLIC_APP_BASE_URL=https://ekko.biratbhattacharjee.com

# --- S3 / MinIO (match **PC-1** data host and `infra/prod/.env.data.example`) ---
# S3_BUCKET=messaging-media
# S3_REGION=us-east-1
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=minio
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=change-me
# S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://<data-hostname-or-IP>:9000
# S3_ANONYMOUS_GET_OBJECT=true
# RABBITMQ_USER=messaging
# RABBITMQ_PASS=change-me
# JWT_SECRET=change-me
# LOG_LEVEL=info

# --- TURN (data host `coturn` + web-client **VITE_*** at build time — see `infra/prod/.env.data.example` § coturn) ---
# COTURN_REALM=ekko.biratbhattacharjee.com
# COTURN_EXTERNAL_IP=<data-host-public-IPv4>
# COTURN_LT_USER=turn
# COTURN_LT_PASS=change-me
# (Web client build) VITE_WEBRTC_TURN_URLS=turn:<ip>:3478,turn:<ip>:3478?transport=tcp
# VITE_WEBRTC_TURN_USERNAME=turn
# VITE_WEBRTC_TURN_CREDENTIAL=change-me
# VITE_WEBRTC_STUN_URLS=stun:stun.l.google.com:19302

# --- k6 scripts (convention) — not read by the apps; export when running k6 from your shell or CI ---
# BASE_URL=https://ekko.biratbhattacharjee.com
# (optional) k6 may use a bearer or cookie from a separate `login` step — do not put long-lived tokens in a committed file.
